<!-- THE BRIEF -->
<p class="section-label cs-mb-24">/ The Brief</p>
<h2 class="h2 cs-mb-24 cs-max-664">Eight emerging artists. Two environments.</h2>
<p class="body-lg cs-max-896 cs-mb-24">Three Ireland's City Stages initiative had spent 2023 touring Ireland, giving emerging buskers a platform outside Three stores in Dublin, Limerick, Waterford, Kilkenny and Galway. The culmination was an ensemble performance at Electric Picnic; eight artists, a full backing band, and a surprise guest set from Cian Ducrot.</p>
<p class="body-lg cs-max-896 cs-section-gap">Big Dog was brought in as sole photography partner across the full campaign. That meant two distinct bodies of work: directed artist portraits at Camden Recording Studios in Dublin to announce the City Stages Collective, and full on-site documentation at Stradbally across the festival weekend, performances, crowd, atmosphere, and the Three Charge &amp; Chill activation.</p>

