<!-- ON THE GROUND -->
<p class="section-label cs-mb-24">/ On The Ground</p>
<h2 class="h2 cs-mb-24 cs-max-664">A live festival is a different discipline to a controlled shoot.</h2>
<p class="body-lg cs-max-896 cs-mb-24">The Camden studio portraits were directed, composition, lighting, and artist presentation all considered and controlled. Electric Picnic demanded something different. The Charge &amp; Chill area ran continuously, with artists performing informally alongside the main activation. The All For Music Stage brought the full ensemble performance, a live crowd, and Cian Ducrot joining the collective for a surprise appearance.</p>
<p class="body-lg cs-max-896 cs-section-gap">The brief across both environments was the same: capture the energy clearly enough to serve the campaign, without losing the atmosphere that made the moment worth documenting. No second takes, no controlled light, no reshoots.</p>

